WEBVTT

00:08:28.944 --> 00:08:31.630
and that there's less cost to feeling it.

00:08:32.448 --> 00:08:36.519
Where deep acting does seem to have
more benefits in terms of how you appear,

00:08:36.543 --> 00:08:38.591
how you come across to others,

00:08:38.615 --> 00:08:40.678
and fewer costs to the self.

00:08:41.282 --> 00:08:44.990
(Music)

00:08:45.014 --> 00:08:46.911
AdG: If you want to master deep acting,

00:08:46.935 --> 00:08:50.292
you can probably learn something
from someone who does it for a living.

00:08:50.316 --> 00:08:51.529
On stage.

00:08:51.553 --> 00:08:55.498
John Lithgow: It's truly agonizing,
when you're acting in a bad play,

00:08:55.522 --> 00:08:58.768
because you have to go out and do it,
whether it works or not.

00:08:59.744 --> 00:09:02.077
AdG: You might recognize this voice.